<<<<<How to Run>>>>>

  ================================================================================
    QUICK START
  ================================================================================
    apptainer run --nv container.sif

  (--nv gives access to the GPU. Drop it only on a CPU-only host.)


  ================================================================================
    MODES & FLAGS
  ================================================================================
    MODES
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
      jupyter (default)      JupyterLab
        apptainer run --nv --bind /my/code:/code container.sif jupyter

      tensorboard            TensorBoard, pointed at /output
        apptainer run --nv --bind /my/output:/output container.sif tensorboard

      jupyter+tensorboard    Both together (TensorBoard in background, Jupyter foreground)
        apptainer run --nv --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/output:/output \
          container.sif jupyter+tensorboard

    FLAGS
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
      --nv                --nv        (NVIDIA GPUs)
      --rocm              --rocm      (AMD GPUs, instead of --nv)
      --bind src:dst      --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/data:/data --bind /my/output:/output
      --env KEY=VALUE     --env CUDA_VISIBLE_DEVICES=0

    Directories to bind: /code /data /output /model /scratch


  ================================================================================
    RUN YOUR OWN SCRIPT (EXEC)
  ================================================================================
    apptainer exec --nv \
      --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/data:/data --bind /my/output:/output \
      container.sif python /code/train.py

    # Multiple GPUs on one node (Horovod, ships in this image)
    apptainer exec --nv --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/data:/data \
      container.sif horovodrun -np 4 python /code/train.py


  ================================================================================
    SLURM — SINGLE NODE
  ================================================================================
    #!/bin/bash
    #SBATCH --job-name=tf-train
    #SBATCH --gres=gpu:4
    #SBATCH --ntasks-per-node=1
    #SBATCH --cpus-per-task=32
    #SBATCH --partition=gpu
    #SBATCH --output=./logs/logs_%j.out
    #SBATCH --error=./logs/logs_%j.err
    #SBATCH --time=04:00:00

    echo "===================================="
    echo "Job Name   : $SLURM_JOB_NAME"
    echo "GPUs       : $SLURM_GPUS_ON_NODE"
    echo "===================================="

    srun apptainer exec --nv \
      --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/data:/data --bind /my/output:/output \
      container.sif \
      horovodrun -np 4 python /code/train.py

    echo "===================================="
    echo "Training Completed"
    echo "===================================="


  ================================================================================
    SLURM — MULTI-NODE  (MultiWorkerMirroredStrategy, TF_CONFIG built from
                         Slurm env — house-style logs/echo banners added)
  ================================================================================
    #!/bin/bash
    #SBATCH --job-name=tf-train-multinode
    #SBATCH --nodes=2
    #SBATCH --gres=gpu:4
    #SBATCH --ntasks-per-node=1
    #SBATCH --cpus-per-task=32
    #SBATCH --output=./logs/logs_%j.out
    #SBATCH --error=./logs/logs_%j.err
    #SBATCH --time=04:00:00

    export MASTER_ADDR=$(scontrol show hostnames "$SLURM_JOB_NODELIST" | head -n1)
    export MASTER_PORT=29500

    echo "===================================="
    echo "Job Name   : $SLURM_JOB_NAME"
    echo "Master Addr: $MASTER_ADDR"
    echo "Nodes      : $SLURM_NNODES"
    echo "===================================="

    srun --ntasks-per-node=1 apptainer exec --nv \
      --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/data:/data --bind /my/output:/output \
      container.sif \
      python /code/train.py

    echo "===================================="
    echo "Training Completed"
    echo "===================================="

    train.py builds TF_CONFIG itself from $SLURM_PROCID, $SLURM_JOB_NODELIST,
    and MASTER_ADDR/MASTER_PORT above, then calls
    tf.distribute.MultiWorkerMirroredStrategy().

    Alternative — Horovod over MPI instead of TF_CONFIG:
      srun --ntasks-per-node=4 apptainer exec --nv \
        --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/data:/data \
        container.sif python /code/train.py   # script calls hvd.init()

    On Ethernet-only nodes add: --env NCCL_IB_DISABLE=1 --env NCCL_SOCKET_IFNAME=eth0
    (InfiniBand nodes need nothing extra — NCCL auto-detects.)


  ================================================================================
    CHECKING IT WORKS
  ================================================================================
    apptainer test --nv container.sif

